
				 BPL

		   Bigraphical Programming Language

		      Standard ML Implementation


This software is a Standard ML implementation of BPL, the Bigraphical
Programming Language.  It is created and maintained by the BPL group
at the IT University of Copenhagen.

For more information, see
http://www.itu.dk/research/pls/wiki/index.php/Bigraphical_Programming_Languages_%28BPL%29


DOCUMENTATION LOCATIONS
=======================

The BPL Tool home page contains documentation for users as well as
developers

  http://www.itu.dk/research/pls/wiki/index.php/BPL_Tool

Some documentation is also included in the source distribution, as
described below.

Where to find documentation for specific topics is descibed in the
following list:

  INSTALL   For information on how to install BPL, see the file named
            INSTALL. For a more thorough description, see

              http://www.itu.dk/research/pls/wiki/index.php/BPL_Tool_Installation_instructions

  DIRTREE   For information on directory structure, see the file
            named DIRTREE, which is autogenerated by running

              make DIRTREE

  API       API documentation is available at

              http://www.itu.dk/research/theory/bpl/doc/ml/doc/

            It can also be generated from the source files using the
            SMLDoc tool available from the SML# Project at

              http://www.pllab.riec.tohoku.ac.jp/smlsharp/?SMLDoc 

  THEORY    For theoretical and background information on BPL, see

              http://www.itu.dk/research/pls/wiki/index.php/Bigraphical_Programming_Languages_%28BPL%29

            For theoretical information on implementation of normalisation, see
            doc/bplimpl/bplimpl.tex in the BPL SVN repository.

  VERSION   For version information, see the file named VERSION.

  LICENSE   For licencing information, see the file named COPYING.


DOWNLOAD
========

The BPL SML package is available from
http://www.itu.dk/research/pls/wiki/index.php/BPL_Tool_Download


TESTING
=======

Testing can be done by entering

  make test

at the command line.


REPORTING BUGS
==============

Well-documented bug reports should be sent to bpl-bugs at itu dot dk.
